text: Ajike Ogunoye was a paramount ruler of Owo Kingdom, Ondo state, southwestern Nigeria who reigned between 1938 and 1941. He was the son of Olagbegi Atanneye I and immediate brother of Olowo Ajaka. ==References== Category:Yoruba monarchs Category:Nigerian traditional rulers Category:People from Owo Category:Olagbegi family
title: Ajike Ogunoye
